Text.Value: Wrong - it belongs to me.
Let me guess - some kind of golem crime boss?
Lucky you.
I reckon I deserve a reward for killing his agents.
Surely he can't stand against the Guild?
I deserve a little something for helping you.
Now scram.
What were his agents doing here?
Happy to help - who did we just kill?
I deserve a little something for helping protect your operations.
I'll leave you to your spoils then. Goodbye.
Agents of the Stone Lord.
They were shifting something valuable by boat. But that something belongs to the Guild now.
The real criminals are the patriars slapping each other on the back in Wyrm's Rock while the people die in the streets.
So am I - I'll be taking everything.
Scurry off back to the streets now.
The Guild keeps order - and looks out for the little man.
Traitorous little guttersnipe - I'll cut you to offal!
I'm rather ruthless too. Time to die.
Sounds ominous.
But human. We think. And definitely ruthless.
Stone Lord? Never heard of him.
He is. Nobody has actually seen him, but word is he's tough as rocks, and ruthless as an ettin.
I'd prefer gold to gratitude.
A new flavour of scum that's been muscling in on our business.
He's a newcomer to our delightful underworld. And he doesn't play nice with others.
Leave.
We think he's in league with the Absolute cultists. This little operation here certainly suggests so.
Nobody actually knows. Word is he's big, dense, tough as rocks.
Who were they?
Leave.
Who did I just kill to earn that coin?
They wouldn't earn the gratitude of the Guild.
Really? Does anyone actually believe that?
Are you going to pay me for helping clean up this scum?
The Guild always wins in the end. But this Stone Lord is trouble.
Leave.
We think the Stone Lord and his cronies are in league with the Absolute cultists. This little operation here certainly suggests so.
One usually follows the other. Here you go.
You did good, stranger. Some would have tried to slink away rather than get involved.

EditorData.NodeContext: Clearly a little too into the bloody combat she has just won

Text.Value: I heard the Stone Lord's name from a dying man. Who is he?
Thanks for the tip - I'll bear that in mind. Goodbye.
You'd be surprised.
Leave.
Of course - the Guild always rewards good work.
I don't play nice with others either - time to die.
I don't particularly want gratitude from criminals.

Synopsis: The battle has ended with all the Smugglers dead. The Attacker Leader Farlin must have survived.
